 Chwojnik emigrated, via Czechoslovakia and Austria, to Israel, where he\nhad changed name to Menachem Oren. In 1951, he won the Israeli championship and\nthe Tel Aviv City championship. In 1952, he won again the Tel Aviv City\nchampionship. Wolsza Tadeusz, Arcymistrzowie, mistrzowie, amatorzy. SÅownik\nbiograficzny szachistÃ³w polskich, tom 5. Wydawnictwo DiG, Warszawa 2007. ISBN\n83-7181-495-X\n\nHe played thrice for Israel in Chess Olympiads: at second board (+6 â4 =3) at\nHelsinki 1952, third board (+7 â2 =3) at Amsterdam 1954, and fourth board (+2 â2\n=4) at Moscow 1956. [http://www.olimpbase.org OlimpBase :: the encyclopaedia\nof team chess ]\n","linknr":137,"url":"Menachem_Oren","recorded":1375073995,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Menachem_Oren&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Menachem_Oren&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/1.e4.png/20px-1.e4.png","/wiki/Algebraic_notation_(chess)","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/12/Flag_of_Poland.svg/23px-Flag_of_Poland.svg.png","/wiki/Poland","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d4/Flag_of_Israel.svg/21px-Flag_of_Israel.svg.png","/wiki/Israel","/wiki/Ruzhany","/wiki/Tel_A